"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-11-01-t-t-host-inaugural-special-olympics-regional-beach-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PORT OF SPAIN, Trinidad (CMC) - Trinidad & Tobago is set to create history next month when it plays home to the first-ever Special Olympics Regional Beach Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Spain\", \"score\": 0.9999964325158969, \"rank\": 3.1287776770094205e-06, \"text\": \"PORT OF SPAIN\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 23, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\", \"score\": 0.9963638143534553, \"rank\": 0.00364931022423448, \"text\": \"Trinidad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\"}, {\"begin\": 25, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commandant_of_the_Marine_Corps\", \"score\": 0.9394809310944254, \"rank\": 0.06202095475666184, \"text\": \"CMC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commandant_of_the_Marine_Corps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commandant_of_the_Marine_Corps\"}, {\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999422060472, \"rank\": 5.710579369701164e-08, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games is scheduled to run from November 8 to 10 and is being facilitated by Special Olympics T&T (SOTT), with the Digicel Foundation as one of the event's main sponsors.\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 243, \"end\": 259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999422060472, \"rank\": 5.710579369701164e-08, \"text\": \"Special Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Special_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digicel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Digicel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digicel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digicel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will feature 130 athletes, 70 coaches, and delegates from 14 Special Olympics programmes across the Caribbean and North America, who will compete in a variety of beach sports, including aquathlon, beach bocce, beach soccer, beach volleyball and open water swimming, at venues in both Trinidad and Tobago.\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\", \"score\": 0.9963638143534553, \"rank\": 0.00364931022423448, \"text\": \"Trinidad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trinidad_and_Tobago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Digicel Foundation Chief Executive Officer Penny Gomez said the company was pleased to be associated with such an important event.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 777, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny\", \"score\": 0.9890132207506988, \"rank\": 0.008544399143030967, \"text\": \"Penny\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selena_Gomez\", \"score\": 0.9932379519055436, \"rank\": 0.005632983268971603, \"text\": \"Gomez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selena_Gomez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selena_Gomez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The dedication and commitment demonstrated by our special athletes and coaches is nothing short of inspiring.\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a great honour for T&T to have been selected to host the inaugural Special Olympics Regional Beach Games, and this recognition of our very own SOTT is very well-deserved,\\\" Gomez said.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1069, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selena_Gomez\", \"score\": 0.9932379519055436, \"rank\": 0.005632983268971603, \"text\": \"Gomez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selena_Gomez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Selena_Gomez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": []}]}"